1 SECTION 3. Requirement to participate in a battery producer responsibility organization.
2 (1) A covered producer may not sell, offer for sale or distribute in or into this state a covered
3 product unless the covered producer satisfies the requirements of sections 2 to 17 of this 2026
4 Act by participating in a battery producer responsibility organization that successfully im-
5 plements a battery producer responsibility program.
6 (2) The failure of a battery producer responsibility organization to satisfy any of the re-
7 sponsibilities delegated to it by a covered producer for developing and implementing a battery
8 producer responsibility program does not relieve the covered producer of the covered
9 producer’s responsibility to satisfy the requirements of sections 2 to 17 of this 2026 Act.
10 SECTION 4. Plans for battery producer responsibility programs. (1) In the form and
11 manner prescribed by the Department of Environmental Quality, a battery producer re-
12 sponsibility organization shall submit to the department a plan for implementing a battery
13 producer responsibility program as provided in this section.
14 (2) A battery producer responsibility program plan must describe how the battery pro-
15 ducer responsibility organization will implement a battery producer responsibility program
16 that satisfies the requirements of sections 2 to 17 of this 2026 Act. The plan must include:
17 (a) A list of all covered producers participating in the battery producer responsibility
18 organization and a list of each brand of covered product sold, offered for sale or distributed
19 in or into this state by each participating covered producer.
20 (b) A description of how the battery producer responsibility organization will:
21 (A) Provide for the responsible management of covered batteries consistent with section
22 8 of this 2026 Act and the policies set forth in ORS 459.015 (2).
23 (B) Provide for convenient and equitable service as required by section 7 of this 2026 Act,
24 including a list of all service providers involved in the management of collected batteries,
25 including all collection sites, transporters and processors the battery producer responsibility
26 organization will contract with or use to provide services required by sections 2 to 17 of this
27 2026 Act.
28 (C) Provide for education and public awareness as required by section 9 of this 2026 Act,
29 including a description of the biennial survey to measure public awareness required by sec-
30 tion 9 of this 2026 Act.
31 (D) Establish a schedule of membership fees sufficient to meet the financial obligations
32 of the battery producer responsibility organization as described in section 11 of this 2026 Act.
33 (E) Ensure continuous improvement of the battery producer responsibility program by
34 establishing and working to achieve measurable performance goals for the program. Per-
35 formance goals must include the date by which the goal will be met. Beginning with the
36 fourth program year and thereafter, performance goals must include annual goals for:
37 (i) Collection rates;
38 (ii) Recycling efficiency; and
39 (iii) Achieving, maintaining and improving high public awareness of the program, includ-
40 ing awareness in low-income, rural and other historically underserved communities.
41 (F) Coordinate with other battery producer responsibility organizations, if applicable.
42 (c) A program budget that describes how the battery producer responsibility organization
43 will finance the battery producer responsibility program, with all costs to carry out a pro-
44 gram that satisfies the requirements of sections 2 to 17 of this 2026 Act apportioned among
45 each covered producer participating in the battery producer responsibility organization, as
