21 SECTION 8. Responsible management. (1) A battery producer responsibility organization
22 shall, in compliance with all applicable laws, ensure that the organization’s battery producer
23 responsibility program uses responsible management in collecting, transporting, processing,
24 recycling or otherwise managing covered batteries and materials from covered batteries.
25 Responsible management includes:
26 (a) Adequate record keeping;
27 (b) Tracking the fate of covered batteries;
28 (c) Conducting performance audits and inspections;
29 (d) Complying with worker health and safety requirements;
30 (e) Ensuring that materials from covered batteries are delivered to responsible end
31 markets;
32 (f) Maintaining liability insurance and other financial assurances; and
33 (g) Carrying out other practices related to the duties of a battery producer responsibility
34 organization, as may be adopted by rule by the Environmental Quality Commission.
35 (2) A battery producer responsibility organization shall ensure that all collection sites
36 and processors that manage covered batteries or materials from covered batteries collected
37 through the battery producer responsibility program use responsible management with re-
38 spect to covered batteries and materials from covered batteries.
39 SECTION 9. Public education and awareness. (1) A battery producer responsibility or-
40 ganization shall develop educational resources and conduct public awareness activities across
41 multiple types of media to advertise and promote, on a regular basis, recycling of covered
42 batteries and collection opportunities statewide. In addition, a battery producer responsibility
43 organization shall:
44 (a) Establish a toll-free telephone number and a website address that a covered entity
45 may use to contact the battery producer responsibility organization to provide feedback
[8]

